<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="571" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,222,787]" pageId="10" pageNumber="571">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,366,391]" pageId="10" pageNumber="571">Description.</emphasis>
This species is very similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Liu &amp; Shen &amp; Gong &amp; Zhang &amp; He" authorityYear="2019" box="[708,882,366,391]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Mecopoda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="571" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hainanensis">
<emphasis box="[708,731,367,390]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="571">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[748,882,366,391]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="571">hainanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[900,991,366,391]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1878,1900]" captionTargetBox="[304,1286,491,1845]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[304,1286,491,1845]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Mecopoda spp. from China. A-C: M. elongata elongata, DE: M. fallax sp. nov., FG: M. niponensis, HI: M. hainanensis sp. nov., J: M. mamorata sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2640102/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="571">Fig. 2D</figureCitation>
), but the forewing is parallel in lateral view (the forewing of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Liu &amp; Shen &amp; Gong &amp; Zhang &amp; He" authorityYear="2019" box="[401,572,402,427]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Mecopoda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="571" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hainanensis">
<emphasis box="[401,424,404,427]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="571">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[438,572,402,427]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="571">hainanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is narrow in basal half and wide in apical half in lateral view).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,222,787]" box="[199,813,438,463]" pageId="10" pageNumber="571">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,293,438,463]" pageId="10" pageNumber="571">Female.</emphasis>
Similar to male. Ovipositor straight (
<figureCitation box="[713,800,438,463]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1878,1900]" captionTargetBox="[304,1286,491,1845]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[304,1286,491,1845]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Mecopoda spp. from China. A-C: M. elongata elongata, DE: M. fallax sp. nov., FG: M. niponensis, HI: M. hainanensis sp. nov., J: M. mamorata sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2640102/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="571">Fig. 2E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,222,787]" pageId="10" pageNumber="571">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,474,499]" pageId="10" pageNumber="571">Coloration.</emphasis>
Nearly brown. 0-2 black spots on the base of forewing. In same individual, the number of the black spots on left and right wing may be different.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1122,546,571]" pageId="10" pageNumber="571" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,222,787]" box="[199,1122,546,571]" pageId="10" pageNumber="571">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,546,571]" pageId="10" pageNumber="571">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Liu &amp; Shen &amp; Gong &amp; Zhang &amp; He" authorityYear="2019" box="[459,523,546,571]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Mecopoda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="571" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fallax">
<emphasis box="[459,523,546,571]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="571">fallax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is used to emphasize its similarity to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Liu &amp; Shen &amp; Gong &amp; Zhang &amp; He" authorityYear="2019" box="[944,1115,546,571]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Mecopoda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="571" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hainanensis">
<emphasis box="[944,967,548,571]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="571">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[981,1115,546,571]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="571">hainanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="571" type="description">
