<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="571" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,222,787]" pageId="10" pageNumber="571">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,262,726,751]" pageId="10" pageNumber="571">Note.</emphasis>
This species is only found from 
<collectingRegion box="[645,734,727,750]" country="China" name="Yunnan" pageId="10" pageNumber="571">Yunnan</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[747,818,726,751]" name="China" pageId="10" pageNumber="571">China</collectingCountry>
. In Mangshi (Dehong, 
<collectingRegion box="[1085,1174,727,750]" country="China" name="Yunnan" pageId="10" pageNumber="571">Yunnan</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1187,1258,726,751]" name="China" pageId="10" pageNumber="571">China</collectingCountry>
), we found this species was sympatric and synchronous with 
<taxonomicName authority="elongata" authorityName="elongata (Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[659,900,762,787]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Mecopoda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="571" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="elongata" subSpecies="elongata">
<emphasis box="[659,682,764,787]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="571">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[697,900,762,787]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="571">elongata elongata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
